PN,30401
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774598699
OL,3,CTesco and Sainsbury's non-loyalty
OL,4,Cbrand prices more expensive than
OL,5,CWaitrose
OL,7,FTesco and Sainsbury's customers are
OL,8,Fpaying more than Waitrose shoppers for
OL,9,Fsome common branded groceries if they
OL,10,Fare not using a loyalty scheme,
OL,11,Fanalysis by Which? has found.
OL,13,FThe watchdog compared a list of 245
OL,14,Fbranded items including Heinz, Nescafe
OL,15,Fand Mr Kipling in February, finding
OL,16,Fthat it was, on average, most
OL,17,Fexpensive for customers at Sainsbury's
OL,18,Fand Tesco who were not using the
OL,19,FNectar or Clubcard loyalty schemes.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774598699
OL,3,CTesco and Sainsbury's non-loyalty
OL,4,Cbrand prices more expensive than
OL,5,CWaitrose
OL,7,FWhich? acknowledged that most shoppers
OL,8,Fare part of a membership scheme, but
OL,9,Fsaid some may be unwilling to sign up
OL,10,Fto loyalty cards for reasons such as
OL,11,Fdata privacy, while others have no
OL,12,Fchoice because of eligibility criteria.
OL,14,FTesco customers who are under 18 can
OL,15,Fnot sign up to a Clubcard, although
OL,16,Fthe supermarket has announced it will
OL,17,Freview this before the end of the year.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774598699
OL,3,CTesco and Sainsbury's non-loyalty
OL,4,Cbrand prices more expensive than
OL,5,CWaitrose
OL,7,FThe Which? list of items was most
OL,8,Fexpensive at Sainsbury's for non-
OL,9,FNectar members at #942.66 ` 14% more
OL,10,Fthan the cheapest retailer in the
OL,11,Fstudy Asda, which cost #823.58.
OL,13,FTesco followed behind Sainsbury's,
OL,14,Fwith its non-Clubcard price totalling
OL,15,F11% more than Asda at #916.56.
OL,17,FWhich? said it did not include
OL,18,Fdiscounters Aldi and Lidl in the study
OL,19,Fbecause they did not stock a
OL,20,Fsufficiently large range of branded
OL,21,Fgoods.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774598699
OL,3,CTesco and Sainsbury's non-loyalty
OL,4,Cbrand prices more expensive than
OL,5,CWaitrose
OL,7,FBoth Tesco and Sainsbury's ` the UK's
OL,8,Ftwo largest grocers ` were more
OL,9,Fexpensive for non-members of their
OL,10,Floyalty schemes than Waitrose, which
OL,11,Fcost #899.05.
OL,13,FWaitrose was 9% more expensive than
OL,14,FAsda and emerged as a "more
OL,15,Fcompetitive option", Which? said.
OL,26,@vD@WOUwD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
