FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774598699
OL,3,CTesco and Sainsbury's non-loyalty
OL,4,Cbrand prices more expensive than
OL,5,CWaitrose
OL,7,FWhich? said the figures showed the
OL,8,F"dramatic price gulf" created by
OL,9,Floyalty pricing.
OL,11,FIn one example at Tesco, Which? found
OL,12,Fa 200ml bottle of L'Oreal Paris Elvive
OL,13,FBond Repair Shampoo was double the
OL,14,Fprice on average for shoppers without
OL,15,Fa Clubcard ` at #13 compared to #6.50.
OL,17,FThe higher price was also found at
OL,18,Fboth Morrisons and Sainsbury's.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774598699
OL,3,CTesco and Sainsbury's non-loyalty
OL,4,Cbrand prices more expensive than
OL,5,CWaitrose
OL,7,FWhich? found that a 200g jar of Kenco
OL,8,FSmooth coffee cost shoppers at Tesco
OL,9,Fand Sainsbury's without a loyalty card
OL,10,F#8.35 ` the highest price on the
OL,11,Fmarket.
OL,13,FIn contrast, the same jar was #7 at
OL,14,FWaitrose and #6.32 at Asda, on average.
OL,16,FSimilarly, Waitrose had the cheapest
OL,17,Faverage price for Nescafe Gold Blend
OL,18,Fat #6.25, while non-members at
OL,19,FSainsbury's were asked to pay #8.35.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774598699
OL,3,CTesco and Sainsbury's non-loyalty
OL,4,Cbrand prices more expensive than
OL,5,CWaitrose
OL,7,FMeanwhile, Which? found customers who
OL,8,Fused a Nectar card at Sainsbury's
OL,9,Fcould expect to pay only 3% more than
OL,10,FAsda at #848.56 for the entire list of
OL,11,Fitems.
OL,13,FMorrisons averaged 4% more expensive
OL,14,Fthan Asda when using a More card and
OL,15,F5% more expensive without one.
OL,17,FOcado was also 5% more expensive than
OL,18,FAsda.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774598699
OL,3,CTesco and Sainsbury's non-loyalty
OL,4,Cbrand prices more expensive than
OL,5,CWaitrose
OL,7,FWhich? retail editor Reena Sewraz
OL,8,Fsaid: "Our analysis reveals a shocking
OL,9,Ftruth and shows the impact loyalty
OL,10,Fschemes have had on grocery pricing.
OL,12,F"Branded favourites can actually be
OL,13,Fcheaper at Waitrose than at the UK's
OL,14,Fbiggest supermarkets for shoppers who
OL,15,Fdon't use a loyalty card ` something
OL,16,Fthat would have seemed unthinkable
OL,17,Funtil a few years ago.
OL,26,@pD@GOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
